I made the biggest mistake by ordering their Monte Cristo sandwich, I'm addicted now. This place is the greatest option to have a fast lunch near Columbia, their sandwiches are amazing and the salads are pretty solid too. An absolute favorite in the Morningside Heights area. Killer whiskey selection, killer cocktails, killer vibe.

Small, cozy with an old school vibe. Friendly bartender. Really good selection of whiskey from your classical to top shelf stuff. Decently priced drinks. Great date spot in your in the neighborhood!

They could hire another bartender during the off hours, and give the one bartender a much needed assistant for rest.  I thought the whisky list, particularly the bourbon, was better than most.  Location is good, service was ok, but the prices are high.
Great bar! good drink selection and friendly bar staff, cant wait to go back.
Great setup for a cozy bar with a good set of house rules to follow. Drinks are well mixed at 'cocktail' prices and they are very tasty. Bathroom was clean.

Solid deli near the Columbia campus. Despite being a small space, they do an amazing job of cramming a huge variety of items and foods. They have a surprisingly good salad bar and a wide array of grab and go food items for between classes. They also have a lot of drugstore items in case you need anything.
Drink whiskey and listen to the bartender’s playlist of ballads. Dark enough for interesting conversation.
Excellent food
Very good bourbon bar choice. The place is cozy. I went with couple of friends and we enjoyed.

Small dark space - incredible whiskey selection and a couple great beers. Some really good cocktails as well. Space is very intimate but it was easy to find a spot. We had the penicillin and were pretty into it. Prices are normal. Great spot in the uws.
Great atmosphere with wonderful bartenders!
Low key, great whiskey drinks, order from the bar.

There’s no real food menu (just cheese plate and a couple other bites) but whiskey selection and cocktail menu is great! Far more whiskey options at Caledonia UWS a little further down on Amsterdam Ave- sister restaurants owned by the same crew.

Nice cocktails and beer selection but not overwhelming.  I had the oaxaca old fashion which had a nice smokey flavor. It's a cosy little bar that wasn't too crowded on a summer Friday.  They also have whisky flights that are a bit price but might try next time.
I love this place, hence why I return to it again and again! Such a wide a wide array of American and Scotch whiskies, a convivial local crowd.
Quiey, intimate and romantic
Outstanding bar.
Small bar, Great whiskey & Bourbon selection. Gets crowded at night. Bar staff very friendly.
Excellent cocktails in a comfortable and dark environment. Great breakfast options if you're there early. And the service is excellent. Stand-out spot for the neighborhood.
hole-in-the-wall whiskey place with a  fine menu. Try their old-fashioned cocktails.

Oh yeah
Awesome spot with fantastic bartenders. The witty banter is a delight.

The Hamilton is a great addition to the neighborhood, and is the best use so far of the small space that has had two other identities over the past several years.  It's owned by the same people who run the whiskey bar Caledonia on Amsterdam between 80th and 81st. Their whisk(e)y selection is huge, and cocktails, beer and a few wines are available too.  Unfortunately, the Hamilton had to cancel its fantastic Sunday brunch last summer due to lack of interest, and they seem to have a tough time holding down enough help in the kitchen to keep their dinner menu available all the time.  But the space is primarily a whiskey bar, and I don't have any complaints with their selection and service!  Its original bartender Allen needs to come back more often, though.
Great cocktails and atmosphere. Also the food is very good

Excellent small venue with very large selection of bourbon and portraits of Alexander Hamilton.  The bartenders are friendly and knowledgeable and it is a good spot to take a small group.  The beer selection on tap is around 6 beers, but well selected.  I highly recommend.

Been coming since it opened. This bar is awesome. All the staff, new and old, are solid, friendly bartenders. Alan, Sarah, Ken, and Joey are the best set of bartenders this world's ever freaking seen. You want whiskey? They've freaking got it, with or without an E, rocks, bitters, peat, or whatever else can come with whiskey. They even have beers and cocktails if you can't handle the pure liquid gold that's a good whiskey.

Great happy hour. Snack menu is really small, so if you're hungry, it's not a place to go to

great bartenders and an impressive cache of bourbon and American whiskey, plus some top-shelf scotch

Great staff (particularly Alan). Good selection of Scottish whiskey. Could do with more Irish whiskey but it's a minor complaint. Great vibe. Quiet, hospitable, social. Great for a few nice drinks on a date or by yourself. Good banter.
Awesome food though the fries are a bit too crispy.  Drinks are great too, though overly pricey.

Cute small intimate spot. The bartender Serika? Or Sarika was a total sweetheart seems to really know her stuff.

My friend and I stumbled upon this place after walking around and looking for a quiet place to sit and talk. While none of us really likes whiskey, the bartender was really helpful and talkative about whiskey. In the end we ordered non-whiskey cocktails, which were also really good.
The bartender, Alan. Looks like he knows what he's doing. Great spot.

Great atmosphere, super cozy...basically where you want to be drinking on a cold evening. Additionally, their classic cocktails are on point!
Great for a date. The grilled cheese is pretty amazing.

Very nice staff, amazing food, amazing drinks, and the aesthetic is just so nice. Weekend brunch is also really good! I love this place. It's a bit on the pricier side so it's no regular stop but it is a top 10 favorite place.

A great, tiny place to get away from it all; they have a wonderful drink selection and the food was all excellent, if a bit stingy on portion size. I think this is the perfect place to go with one or two other people. The space is quite narrow and would not be able to accommodate a large party.
Cozy, upscale atmosphere in a typically college-bar neighborhood. Yet, attainable prices. Music is low. Good for dates and deep conversations with friends late into the night.
Relaxed vibe
Great food and great hospitality Allen is a great dude.
Great stuff overall.

I used to come here all the time when it was The Dam, and I do miss that place and the bartenders. But I must say that the space has been completely revamped and has a nice, low key and classy atmosphere. The food is great, including their grilled cheese and their charcuterie and cheese plate. Great selection of cocktails that are at typical Manhattan prices (well, about $3 less than someplace in The Village, which would approach the vibe of this place). So cocktails are $12, very well executed. And the bartenders are generally nice, particularly the good Scottish lad.  The crowd and feel has changed since the days of The Dam, and I will cherish the memories I made there. But I am happy to welcome this new spot to my neighborhood. Excellent in my experience.
The "Perfect Storm" is an excellent Dark and Stormy with their fresh house-made ginger beer!
Great spot!
The Dam has shut down and has been replaced by The Hamilton. Specialising in bourbons and serving great food, they opened a few weeks ago.
